<!--***********************************************************
*  Example 4:  Using the "sectionWideCheckWork" and 
* "aggregateScores" attributes within a subsection. 
*  Method 1:  Using the 'credit = "1"'' attribute within a
*  <choice></choice> tag to mark correct answer.
************************************************************-->

<section><p><em>Robot/AI trivia game Part 1</em></p>

<p>The "sectionWideCheckWork" and "aggregateScores" attributes can be used within a <tag>subsection</tag><tag>/subsection</tag> to suppress solution checking on individual problems.  This atttribute allows for one single checkwork button to occur at the bottom of the subsection.</p>

<p>In this example, the "correct" choice is marked by assigning credit with the credit attribute within the <tag>choice</tag><tag>/choice</tag> component.</p>


  <subsection sectionWideCheckWork aggregateScores>
  <ol>
    <li>Who is the famous AI in 2001: A Space Odyssey?
      <answer>
        <choiceinput>
          <choice>Sonny</choice>
          <choice>Data</choice>
          <choice credit="1">Hal</choice>
        </choiceinput>
      </answer>
    </li>
    <li>What animated robot from space befriended 9 year old Hogarth Hughes?
      <answer>
        <choiceinput>
          <choice credit = "1">the Iron Gian</choice>
          <choice>Baymax</choice>
          <choice>Bender</choice>
        </choiceinput>
      </answer>
    </li>
    <li>What robot is played by Arnold Schwarzenneger?
      <answer>
        <choiceinput>
          <choice>Machinemensch</choice>
          <choice>RoboCop</choice>
          <choice credit="1">the Terminator</choice>
        </choiceinput>
      </answer>
    </li>
  </ol>
  </subsection>

</section>


